that ticks all his boxes,

00:13:07.942 --> 00:13:09.120
you have to sell him that house.

00:13:09.825 --> 00:13:10.519
And when he says no,

00:13:10.782 --> 00:13:11.277
it's not really no.

00:13:12.126 --> 00:13:12.498
It's no,

00:13:12.842 --> 00:13:13.740
"you haven't convinced me enough."

00:13:15.424 --> 00:13:15.553
No,

00:13:15.720 --> 00:13:16.299
"I'm not ready

00:13:16.320 --> 00:13:16.565
to buy yet."

00:13:18.384 --> 00:13:18.799
Maybe even

00:13:18.799 --> 00:13:19.071
in his head,

00:13:19.440 --> 00:13:19.822
he's thinking, "Damn,

00:13:21.799 --> 00:13:22.251
he's already convinced me,

00:13:22.600 --> 00:13:23.039
but I can't say

00:13:23.061 --> 00:13:23.596
yes right away."

00:13:23.679 --> 00:13:24.014
So he says no.

00:13:26.659 --> 00:13:26.940
Damn,

00:13:26.940 --> 00:13:27.172
he killed me.

00:13:28.039 --> 00:13:28.720
I've got nothing to say.

00:13:29.019 --> 00:13:29.159
Well,

00:13:29.260 --> 00:13:29.619
he's telling you no.

00:13:30.767 --> 00:13:31.360
And there could be

00:13:31.360 --> 00:13:31.715
all sorts of reasons.

00:13:32.945 --> 00:13:33.899
Who here has ever been turned down

00:13:33.921 --> 00:13:34.357
and then finally,

00:13:34.539 --> 00:13:34.639
later on,

00:13:34.700 --> 00:13:35.229
you actually got what you wanted?

00:13:36.043 --> 00:13:36.720
In anything, really.

00:13:36.820 --> 00:13:37.197
It works with

00:13:38.066 --> 00:13:38.698
meeting people too.

00:13:41.919 --> 00:13:42.659
I could give you

00:13:42.659 --> 00:13:43.011
tons of examples,

00:13:43.525 --> 00:13:43.876
even personal ones.

00:13:44.606 --> 00:13:45.038
With my wife,

00:13:46.288 --> 00:13:46.678
she told me no.

00:13:47.921 --> 00:13:48.134
Okay,

00:13:48.679 --> 00:13:48.791
cool.

00:13:49.587 --> 00:13:49.860
Watch me.

00:13:50.620 --> 00:13:50.811
Anyway,

00:13:51.919 --> 00:13:52.630
are you with me?

00:13:53.649 --> 00:13:54.078
So the 'no'

00:13:54.120 --> 00:13:55.080
A no isn't a real no.

00:13:56.404 --> 00:13:56.995
No is just...

00:13:58.061 --> 00:13:58.145
No,

00:13:58.519 --> 00:13:58.897
it's not over.

00:13:59.764 --> 00:14:00.179
Obviously,

00:14:00.523 --> 00:14:01.340
if people reject you

00:14:01.340 --> 00:14:01.731
seven times,

00:14:02.144 --> 00:14:02.700
at some point,

00:14:02.900 --> 00:14:03.004
okay?

00:14:03.683 --> 00:14:04.299
Or seven objections,

00:14:04.640 --> 00:14:04.764
okay?

00:14:05.342 --> 00:14:06.240
But you can always come back later.

00:14:07.828 --> 00:14:08.178
Closing.

00:14:08.539 --> 00:14:09.359
Clarify the terms,

00:14:09.702 --> 00:14:10.359
reduce friction,

00:14:10.822 --> 00:14:11.678
create a sense of urgency.

00:14:12.307 --> 00:14:12.759
If you're here,

00:14:14.009 --> 00:14:14.419
you have what it takes

00:14:14.419 --> 00:14:14.792
to close the deal,

00:14:15.100 --> 00:14:15.200
right,

00:14:15.321 --> 00:14:15.717
we agree

00:14:15.985 --> 00:14:16.639
that if we agree

00:14:16.639 --> 00:14:16.875
on this,

00:14:17.080 --> 00:14:17.279
it's good,

00:14:17.360 --> 00:14:17.639
we're doing the deal.

00:14:17.960 --> 00:14:18.027
So,

00:14:18.342 --> 00:14:19.058
you grab a sheet of paper,

00:14:19.423 --> 00:14:20.418
and you write out the deal.

00:14:21.462 --> 00:14:22.200
Just a plain piece of paper.

00:14:23.389 --> 00:14:23.580
Martine,

00:14:23.883 --> 00:14:24.980
can you send me the sheet?

00:14:25.000 --> 00:14:25.139
Come on,

00:14:25.279 --> 00:14:25.807
let's go sign with Jacques.

00:14:27.214 --> 00:14:27.360
And then,

00:14:27.500 --> 00:14:28.820
we take it and sign,

00:14:29.304 --> 00:14:30.360
we write down the terms and conditions.

00:14:30.687 --> 00:14:30.940
The price,

00:14:31.469 --> 00:14:31.859
the conditions,

00:14:32.424 --> 00:14:32.759
the timelines,

00:14:32.981 --> 00:14:33.071
etc.

00:14:34.349 --> 00:14:34.539
So,

00:14:34.620 --> 00:14:34.975
we agree

00:14:35.306 --> 00:14:35.860
that if we go for it,

00:14:36.186 --> 00:14:36.539
we do the deal.

00:14:37.461 --> 00:14:37.674
Yes,

00:14:37.799 --> 00:14:38.153
we agree?

00:14:38.340 --> 00:14:38.436
Okay,

00:14:38.539 --> 00:14:38.850
we shake hands.

00:14:39.159 --> 00:14:39.404
In Switzerland,

00:14:41.823 --> 00:14:42.759
a verbal deal is a deal.

00:14:44.403 --> 00:14:45.398
When you say it out loud,

00:14:46.327 --> 00:14:46.759
and you both agree,

00:14:46.860 --> 00:14:47.159
that's a deal.

00:14:47.380 --> 00:14:48.339
You can literally

00:14:49.184 --> 00:14:49.938
take that to court

00:14:49.980 --> 00:14:50.188
if you need to.

00:14:50.620 --> 00:14:51.379
I know most people

00:14:51.399 --> 00:14:52.099
need a written contract,

00:14:52.200 --> 00:14:52.871
but at some point,

00:14:53.787 --> 00:14:54.200
there are people

00:14:54.200 --> 00:14:55.279
who still keep their word.

00:14:56.388 --> 00:14:56.779
There are people,

00:14:56.799 --> 00:14:57.355
you shake their hand,

00:14:57.620 --> 00:14:58.294
and you just know they'll come back

00:14:58.539 --> 00:15:00.480
and they'll make the deal.

00:15:01.591 --> 00:15:01.719
So,

00:15:02.344 --> 00:15:02.876
take advantage of that too

00:15:03.568 --> 00:15:04.198
and align yourself

00:15:04.907 --> 00:15:05.419
with those kinds of people.

00:15:06.080 --> 00:15:06.999
Alright?

00:15:07.059 --> 00:15:07.357
So,

00:15:07.562 --> 00:15:08.379
try to close deals that way.

00:15:09.067 --> 00:15:10.019
the three major mistakes.

00:15:10.469 --> 00:15:10.537
First,

00:15:10.943 --> 00:15:11.759
talking price too soon.

00:15:12.784 --> 00:15:13.639
When you don't know

00:15:13.884 --> 00:15:14.918
the real reasons for the sale,

00:15:15.059 --> 00:15:15.455
when you don't have

00:15:15.804 --> 00:15:16.419
the full picture,

00:15:16.760 --> 00:15:18.220
you shouldn't talk about price.

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:19.065
Now,

00:15:19.299 --> 00:15:19.611
if the person,

00:15:19.820 --> 00:15:20.032
they come,

00:15:20.424 --> 00:15:21.019
or the real estate agent,

00:15:21.179 --> 00:15:21.360
they come,

00:15:21.380 --> 00:15:22.078
or whoever,

00:15:22.525 --> 00:15:23.519
in any negotiation,

00:15:23.519 --> 00:15:24.176
the person brings up price,

00:15:24.967 --> 00:15:25.679
okay, let's talk price,

00:15:26.360 --> 00:15:26.755
but me,

00:15:26.960 --> 00:15:27.620
I still don't get

00:15:27.620 --> 00:15:28.318
why you want to sell.

00:15:29.639 --> 00:15:29.725
Me,

00:15:30.059 --> 00:15:30.360
I'm not here

00:15:30.360 --> 00:15:30.817
to waste my time.

00:15:34.445 --> 00:15:35.379
I'm really interested,

00:15:35.919 --> 00:15:36.174
but,

00:15:36.821 --> 00:15:37.118
help me out here,

00:15:37.481 --> 00:15:38.080
what's the real price

00:15:38.080 --> 00:15:38.360
that you actually want?

00:15:38.460 --> 00:15:38.639
because right now,

00:15:38.779 --> 00:15:39.499
your price at 10 million,

00:15:39.679 --> 00:15:39.970
it's just crazy.

00:15:40.360 --> 00:15:40.799
You know very well,

00:15:40.879 --> 00:15:41.413
the market will only give you 6,

00:15:42.879 --> 00:15:42.965
Me,

00:15:43.279 --> 00:15:43.679
maybe I'm willing

00:15:44.288 --> 00:15:44.878
to go a bit higher.

00:15:45.480 --> 00:15:45.779
But,

00:15:45.879 --> 00:15:45.947
10,

00:15:46.139 --> 00:15:46.658
that's a no-go.

00:15:47.899 --> 00:15:48.299
You see,

00:15:49.366 --> 00:15:49.919
that's just an example.

00:15:51.200 --> 00:15:51.499
So,

00:15:51.663 --> 00:15:52.398
we'll talk about the price later

00:15:52.500 --> 00:15:52.711
and then,

00:15:53.163 --> 00:15:54.600
you can bounce back on the rest.

00:15:54.940 --> 00:15:55.022
OK?

00:15:55.903 --> 00:15:56.720
When you have someone

00:15:56.740 --> 00:15:57.035
who tells you,

00:15:58.087 --> 00:15:58.259
OK,

00:15:59.746 --> 00:16:00.080
but,

00:16:00.765 --> 00:16:01.460
I want the money right away

00:16:01.886 --> 00:16:02.700
or there's another concession,

00:16:03.241 --> 00:16:04.753
try to negotiate differently.

00:16:07.325 --> 00:16:08.059
I explained it downstairs,

00:16:08.139 --> 00:16:08.716
but I think it's good

00:16:09.063 --> 00:16:09.740
to explain it to you here,

00:16:10.003 --> 00:16:10.820
kind of like a negotiation

00:16:10.820 --> 00:16:11.436
we're having right now.

00:16:11.761 --> 00:16:12.659
We're selling a house.

00:16:13.681 --> 00:16:13.764
OK?

00:16:14.442 --> 00:16:15.336
48.9 million dirhams.

00:16:16.248 --> 00:16:16.398
Listed.

00:16:17.500 --> 00:16:18.220
The real estate agent,

00:16:18.220 --> 00:16:18.678
he comes to me and says,

00:16:18.799 --> 00:16:19.759
"I've got someone who wants to buy the house,

00:16:19.879 --> 00:16:20.539
but they want a payment plan."

00:16:20.700 --> 00:16:20.860
I say,

00:16:20.860 --> 00:16:21.460
"We don't do payment plans."

00:16:22.827 --> 00:16:23.120
But,

00:16:24.884 --> 00:16:25.577
if he's ready to pay

00:16:26.423 --> 00:16:27.015
50% right away

00:16:27.962 --> 00:16:29.220
and 50% by the end of the year,

00:16:29.784 --> 00:16:30.418
at a higher price,

00:16:31.822 --> 00:16:32.700
maybe I can offer that,

00:16:32.779 --> 00:16:33.740
I can work it out with the seller.

00:16:35.341 --> 00:16:35.495
OK,

00:16:35.559 --> 00:16:35.976
I'll get back to you,

00:16:36.159 --> 00:16:36.360
I'll talk to him about it.

00:16:36.720 --> 00:16:36.799
OK.

00:16:37.559 --> 00:16:37.663
48.9,

00:16:38.140 --> 00:16:38.437
we're coming back,

00:16:38.600 --> 00:16:39.240
we're agreeing

00:16:39.240 --> 00:16:39.385
on 51.

00:16:40.769 --> 00:16:41.019
We'll see,

00:16:41.120 --> 00:16:41.360
I'm not convinced,

00:16:41.441 --> 00:16:42.072
it's not closed yet.

00:16:43.320 --> 00:16:43.615
But hey,

00:16:43.820 --> 00:16:44.100
listen up,

00:16:44.847 --> 00:16:44.933
51,

00:16:46.808 --> 00:16:47.139
that's still

00:16:48.543 --> 00:16:49.438
over a million dollars more.

00:16:50.019 --> 00:16:50.244
Right?

00:16:51.480 --> 00:16:51.730
He tells me,

00:16:52.039 --> 00:16:52.120
yeah,

00:16:52.200 --> 00:16:52.500
but on the other hand,

00:16:52.580 --> 00:16:53.559
we need to take the villa off the market

00:16:53.580 --> 00:16:53.995
for two months.

00:16:56.539 --> 00:16:56.879
I say,

00:16:56.940 --> 00:16:57.120
but me,

00:16:57.179 --> 00:16:58.000
I'm not taking the villa off the market

00:16:58.000 --> 00:16:58.379
for two months.

00:16:59.066 --> 00:16:59.379
Unless,

00:17:02.004 --> 00:17:02.860
you give me a million dirhams,

00:17:04.079 --> 00:17:04.409
250,000 dollars,

00:17:04.960 --> 00:17:05.180
right now,

00:17:05.299 --> 00:17:05.799
that you're ready to lose

00:17:06.140 --> 00:17:07.000
so I can take the house off the market.

00:17:09.644 --> 00:17:10.140
Let me get back to you.

00:17:10.586 --> 00:17:10.880
He comes back,

00:17:11.060 --> 00:17:11.519
we agree

00:17:11.539 --> 00:17:11.945
on 850,000 dirhams.

00:17:14.181 --> 00:17:15.380
to take the house off the market

00:17:15.626 --> 00:17:16.059
for two months.

00:17:18.266 --> 00:17:18.878
That means,

00:17:19.000 --> 00:17:19.086
yeah,

00:17:19.443 --> 00:17:19.817
200,000 euros.

00:17:20.662 --> 00:17:22.558
So that means by the end of April,

00:17:23.567 --> 00:17:23.759
so now,

00:17:23.880 --> 00:17:24.039
basically,

00:17:24.304 --> 00:17:24.960
before signing,

00:17:25.503 --> 00:17:25.999
I've got a check,

00:17:26.403 --> 00:17:27.140
not a regular check,

00:17:27.423 --> 00:17:27.939
a cashier's check.

00:17:28.819 --> 00:17:29.218
I tell him,

00:17:29.381 --> 00:17:30.359
you give me the cashier's check,

00:17:32.185 --> 00:17:32.898
we sign the contract,

00:17:34.505 --> 00:17:35.500
I take the villa off the market

00:17:35.766 --> 00:17:36.278
until the end of April.

00:17:37.346 --> 00:17:38.160
You have until the end of April

00:17:38.160 --> 00:17:38.413
to let me know

00:17:38.762 --> 00:17:39.960
if you want to buy the house or not.

00:17:41.385 --> 00:17:42.039
If you say no,

00:17:43.339 --> 00:17:43.618
we part ways,

00:17:43.700 --> 00:17:43.935
no hard feelings,

00:17:44.059 --> 00:17:44.453
and I keep the check.

00:17:45.440 --> 00:17:46.200
That's in the contract.

00:17:48.090 --> 00:17:48.319
But seriously,

00:17:48.805 --> 00:17:49.319
you do agree

00:17:49.545 --> 00:17:50.259
that someone who's willing

00:17:50.525 --> 00:17:51.279
to put down money like that

00:17:51.279 --> 00:17:51.549
on the table,

00:17:52.383 --> 00:17:53.599
because he can't be there

00:17:53.824 --> 00:17:54.859
in person to see the house,

00:17:55.000 --> 00:17:55.398
he must really

00:17:55.980 --> 00:17:56.719
seriously want to buy it.

00:17:56.839 --> 00:17:58.400
I gave you the quick version.

00:17:58.824 --> 00:18:00.000
He did three tours,

00:18:00.119 --> 00:18:00.290
videos,

00:18:00.660 --> 00:18:00.769
Zoom calls,

00:18:00.980 --> 00:18:01.193
all that stuff,

00:18:01.544 --> 00:18:02.200
but he just can't travel.

00:18:02.643 --> 00:18:03.680
He really wants to buy it,

00:18:04.123 --> 00:18:04.740
so he's seriously

00:18:04.740 --> 00:18:05.156
for wanting to come.

00:18:05.839 --> 00:18:06.255
Alright?

00:18:06.769 --> 00:18:07.118
I'll keep going.

00:18:07.579 --> 00:18:07.914
So,

00:18:08.221 --> 00:18:08.463
he tells us,

00:18:09.926 --> 00:18:10.180
this is live,

00:18:10.359 --> 00:18:11.236
it happened two weeks ago.

00:18:12.125 --> 00:18:13.119
Let me set the scene for you

00:18:13.306 --> 00:18:13.759
for the negotiation.

00:18:13.901 --> 00:18:15.039
We're here to talk about negotiation.

00:18:15.299 --> 00:18:16.059
I'm going to show you

00:18:16.325 --> 00:18:17.019
how detailed you can get

00:18:18.361 --> 00:18:18.920
with an offer

00:18:19.846 --> 00:18:20.338
instead of just saying

00:18:20.869 --> 00:18:20.955
me,

00:18:21.079 --> 00:18:21.420
lots of payment options,

00:18:21.500 --> 00:18:21.720
I don't do that.

00:18:24.026 --> 00:18:24.240
No.

00:18:24.920 --> 00:18:25.176
Wait,

00:18:25.461 --> 00:18:26.180
let's talk about the terms.

00:18:27.544 --> 00:18:28.115
Are you following me?

00:18:29.019 --> 00:18:29.499
So,

00:18:29.940 --> 00:18:30.220
I tell him,

00:18:30.299 --> 00:18:30.400
okay,

00:18:30.539 --> 00:18:30.789
end of the month,

00:18:31.691 --> 00:18:31.940
You tell me

00:18:31.940 --> 00:18:32.343
if you want to buy,

00:18:34.779 --> 00:18:34.938
per year,

00:18:35.019 --> 00:18:35.367
you give me 50%.

00:18:37.107 --> 00:18:37.539
at the end of the month,

00:18:37.619 --> 00:18:38.257
you move into the house,

00:18:39.839 --> 00:18:40.326
but if by December 25th,

00:18:41.279 --> 00:18:41.579
you don't pay

00:18:41.579 --> 00:18:41.890
the other 50%,

00:18:42.482 --> 00:18:43.252
you lose your 50%,

00:18:44.102 --> 00:18:46.240
you have to leave the house

00:18:46.667 --> 00:18:47.299
and I keep the place.

00:18:48.422 --> 00:18:48.551
Okay.

00:18:49.660 --> 00:18:49.897
So,

00:18:50.019 --> 00:18:50.339
it's really

00:18:50.339 --> 00:18:50.753
who wants the house.

00:18:52.384 --> 00:18:53.220
Are we good with that or not?

00:18:53.347 --> 00:18:53.559
So now,

00:18:53.619 --> 00:18:53.796
basically,

00:18:53.941 --> 00:18:54.176
let's see.

00:18:54.563 --> 00:18:55.239
I've already seen the check,

00:18:55.742 --> 00:18:56.818
we got the check,

00:18:56.960 --> 00:18:57.654
we'll see if it actually gets signed or not.

00:18:58.019 --> 00:18:58.258
And so,

00:18:58.339 --> 00:18:58.592
what is it?

00:18:58.780 --> 00:18:59.299
I'm free money,

00:19:00.125 --> 00:19:00.640
I'm a free option.

00:19:01.140 --> 00:19:01.916
I make 200,000 bucks

00:19:02.182 --> 00:19:02.900
just for giving someone the option

00:19:03.288 --> 00:19:03.819
to buy.

00:19:03.819 --> 00:19:03.882
That,

00:19:04.460 --> 00:19:04.720
again,

00:19:04.799 --> 00:19:05.494
we're talking about selling a house.

00:19:06.508 --> 00:19:06.859
For you,

00:19:07.183 --> 00:19:07.940
you can work it

00:19:07.960 --> 00:19:08.449
in different ways.

00:19:09.099 --> 00:19:09.180
So,

00:19:09.363 --> 00:19:10.339
get creative with it.

00:19:11.662 --> 00:19:11.771
Okay.

00:19:12.119 --> 00:19:12.393
Part 2,

00:19:12.826 --> 00:19:13.199
the 10 qualities

00:19:13.444 --> 00:19:14.000
of a good negotiator.

00:19:15.381 --> 00:19:15.615
So,

00:19:16.799 --> 00:19:16.864
this,

00:19:17.240 --> 00:19:18.059
is super important too.

00:19:18.993 --> 00:19:19.079
Win,

00:19:19.200 --> 00:19:19.314
lose.

00:19:19.806 --> 00:19:19.920
So,

00:19:20.105 --> 00:19:20.420
I win,

00:19:20.685 --> 00:19:20.980
you lose.

00:19:21.099 --> 00:19:21.355
Not good.

00:19:22.345 --> 00:19:23.160
That doesn't work in the long run.

00:19:24.107 --> 00:19:24.539
It just won't work.

00:19:25.940 --> 00:19:26.239
So,

00:19:26.463 --> 00:19:26.779
I win,

00:19:26.940 --> 00:19:27.172
you lose.

00:19:27.420 --> 00:19:27.798
That means,

00:19:27.880 --> 00:19:28.074
really,

00:19:28.240 --> 00:19:28.648
there's an imbalance

00:19:29.923 --> 00:19:30.657
between the fact that

00:19:32.640 --> 00:19:32.960
you,

00:19:33.222 --> 00:19:34.480
you really gained something

00:19:34.520 --> 00:19:34.832
and the other person,

00:19:35.324 --> 00:19:36.279
you're kind of ripping them off a bit.

00:19:36.422 --> 00:19:37.276
Basically.

00:19:37.820 --> 00:19:38.098
Careful,

00:19:38.200 --> 00:19:38.755
there are some really great deals.

00:19:39.201 --> 00:19:39.919
You're in a win-win situation

00:19:40.185 --> 00:19:40.759
as soon as

00:19:40.759 --> 00:19:41.079
the other person,

00:19:41.180 --> 00:19:41.420
it's a win for them too.

00:19:41.622 --> 00:19:42.759
But for it to be a loss

00:19:43.211 --> 00:19:43.539
and for the...

00:19:43.539 --> 00:19:43.799
You see,

00:19:44.000 --> 00:19:44.473
that's not good.

00:19:45.700 --> 00:19:46.598
The lose-win,

00:19:46.819 --> 00:19:47.176
obviously,

00:19:47.299 --> 00:19:47.595
we don't go for that.

00:19:48.039 --> 00:19:48.107
Okay.

00:19:49.106 --> 00:19:49.618
The win-win,

00:19:50.285 --> 00:19:50.519
that's good,

00:19:50.720 --> 00:19:53.019
but try to find the win-win-win.

00:19:55.079 --> 00:19:56.816
So what's a win-win-win?

00:19:57.906 --> 00:19:58.460
A win-win-win,

00:19:58.740 --> 00:19:59.179
is when

00:20:00.807 --> 00:20:01.179
I win,

00:20:01.440 --> 00:20:01.559
well,

00:20:01.885 --> 00:20:02.298
you win,

00:20:02.809 --> 00:20:03.160
I win,

00:20:03.442 --> 00:20:04.759
and together we win even more

00:20:05.144 --> 00:20:06.140
because when you add it up,

00:20:06.343 --> 00:20:07.278
we end up doing way more.

00:20:09.347 --> 00:20:09.759
On your side,

00:20:09.980 --> 00:20:10.839
you see what I mean?

00:20:10.839 --> 00:20:10.910
That,

00:20:11.201 --> 00:20:12.358
that works in every partnership,

00:20:12.519 --> 00:20:12.875
every negotiation,

00:20:13.059 --> 00:20:13.153
and so on.

00:20:13.299 --> 00:20:14.539
Try to see what you can find

00:20:15.106 --> 00:20:16.079
at the ultimate level with this.

00:20:16.519 --> 00:20:16.660
So,

00:20:16.740 --> 00:20:17.299
let me give you an example.

00:20:18.847 --> 00:20:19.079
Someone,

00:20:19.180 --> 00:20:19.678
a marchand de biens,

00:20:19.839 --> 00:20:20.579
I was talking to him not long ago,

00:20:20.842 --> 00:20:21.700
he locked in a deal.

00:20:22.726 --> 00:20:23.319
They came to an agreement

00:20:23.644 --> 00:20:25.000
between the investor putting up the money,

00:20:25.502 --> 00:20:26.617
the project leader with the project,

00:20:27.208 --> 00:20:27.799
and he makes the deal happen.

00:20:28.721 --> 00:20:28.880
And this guy,

00:20:29.021 --> 00:20:29.178
he says,

00:20:29.481 --> 00:20:30.480
since his son wants to join him

00:20:30.500 --> 00:20:31.294
in the marchand de biens business,

00:20:31.740 --> 00:20:31.980
he tells him,

00:20:34.669 --> 00:20:34.953
you know what?

00:20:35.709 --> 00:20:36.200
On top of that,

00:20:36.546 --> 00:20:36.940
we do the deal,

00:20:37.405 --> 00:20:38.059
I'll help your son out.

00:20:39.087 --> 00:20:39.559
I'll show him

00:20:39.559 --> 00:20:40.539
what being a marchand de biens is all about,

00:20:40.560 --> 00:20:41.016
and I'll show him

00:20:41.140 --> 00:20:41.493
how to do the whole thing,

00:20:41.720 --> 00:20:41.799
and so on.

00:20:43.901 --> 00:20:44.436
The investor

00:20:44.969 --> 00:20:45.419
who's older

00:20:46.166 --> 00:20:46.700
is really happy

00:20:46.700 --> 00:20:46.846
to see

00:20:47.365 --> 00:20:47.798
that his son

00:20:47.880 --> 00:20:48.084
is going to come

00:20:49.523 --> 00:20:50.159
manage the deal

00:20:50.506 --> 00:20:51.259
and get mentored

00:20:51.788 --> 00:20:52.380
by a marchand de biens.

00:20:52.766 --> 00:20:53.278
It's a win-win,

00:20:53.520 --> 00:20:53.786
win, and win.

00:20:55.788 --> 00:20:56.019
And that,

00:20:56.323 --> 00:20:57.339
can only happen

00:20:57.565 --> 00:20:58.180
when you actually know

00:20:58.766 --> 00:21:00.140
what really motivates people,

00:21:00.503 --> 00:21:01.160
what's going on behind the scenes,

00:21:01.522 --> 00:21:02.378
when you care about their family,

00:21:03.400 --> 00:21:04.140
what they're planning to do

00:21:04.140 --> 00:21:04.792
over the next 5-10 years,

00:21:05.460 --> 00:21:05.920
where they're at

00:21:05.920 --> 00:21:06.213
in their life,

00:21:06.400 --> 00:21:06.535
and so on.

00:21:06.861 --> 00:21:07.491
Are you following me or not?

00:21:08.250 --> 00:21:08.480
Same thing,

00:21:08.705 --> 00:21:09.039
an eco-friendly type.

00:21:09.785 --> 00:21:10.159
An eco-friendly type,

00:21:10.402 --> 00:21:11.259
do a deal with an eco-friendly person,

00:21:11.319 --> 00:21:12.058
you know they're into being green,

00:21:12.362 --> 00:21:12.859
there's a bonus,

00:21:12.881 --> 00:21:13.337
at some point,

00:21:13.440 --> 00:21:14.539
I'm only going to do solar panels,

00:21:14.900 --> 00:21:15.631
I'm only going to do eco stuff,

00:21:16.220 --> 00:21:17.559
we're going to make it an eco-friendly project.

00:21:19.487 --> 00:21:19.900
And you go for it,

00:21:20.059 --> 00:21:20.398
obviously.

00:21:21.339 --> 00:21:21.596
And right there,

00:21:21.720 --> 00:21:22.273
it's a win-win-win,

00:21:22.559 --> 00:21:22.932
plus you create

00:21:23.262 --> 00:21:23.920
an even bigger alpha.

00:21:24.061 --> 00:21:24.660
Do you realize what you're

00:21:24.681 --> 00:21:25.094
actually doing?

00:21:25.280 --> 00:21:25.920
Not only is it good

00:21:25.920 --> 00:21:26.317
for everyone,

00:21:27.066 --> 00:21:27.599
but on top of that,

00:21:27.680 --> 00:21:28.145
it puts you way ahead of

00:21:29.960 --> 00:21:30.491
the rest of the competition,

00:21:30.980 --> 00:21:31.720
who won't even go there.

00:21:32.143 --> 00:21:33.079
People are way too focused on price.

00:21:34.001 --> 00:21:34.377
There are people,

00:21:34.519 --> 00:21:35.098
they couldn't care less

00:21:35.119 --> 00:21:35.486
about money.

00:21:38.044 --> 00:21:38.900
People want to do deals

00:21:38.900 --> 00:21:39.476
with people they like,

00:21:40.500 --> 00:21:41.579
with people they vibe with.

00:21:42.222 --> 00:21:43.239
Me, I don't do business anymore

00:21:44.442 --> 00:21:45.400
or work with partners,

00:21:45.519 --> 00:21:46.460
I don't bring people on board anymore

00:21:46.460 --> 00:21:47.074
if I don't feel like...

00:21:47.442 --> 00:21:48.200
If I know I can't

00:21:48.923 --> 00:21:49.920
have a conversation with you

00:21:49.940 --> 00:21:50.428
and go out to dinner with you

00:21:51.200 --> 00:21:51.753
for two hours and all that,

00:21:51.980 --> 00:21:52.509
because you were annoying,

00:21:53.880 --> 00:21:54.375
I'm just not interested.

00:21:55.481 --> 00:21:56.839
So that's the level

00:21:56.839 --> 00:21:57.314
you need to reach.

00:21:57.884 --> 00:21:58.398
Who wants to deal with

00:21:58.460 --> 00:21:59.075
and work with people

00:21:59.299 --> 00:22:00.858
who are negative,

00:22:02.259 --> 00:22:03.119
only focused on...?

00:22:03.547 --> 00:22:04.199
Am I right or not?

00:22:04.342 --> 00:22:04.920
You want to do deals

00:22:04.920 --> 00:22:05.519
with people you really like,

00:22:05.559 --> 00:22:05.807
yes or no?

00:22:06.826 --> 00:22:07.299
That's why

00:22:07.299 --> 00:22:07.919
communities like this

00:22:07.960 --> 00:22:08.336
are important.

00:22:11.839 --> 00:22:12.720
So, let's keep going.

00:22:13.589 --> 00:22:13.898
Listening.

00:22:15.943 --> 00:22:16.599
Listening isn't the same

00:22:16.599 --> 00:22:16.853
as just hearing.

00:22:18.864 --> 00:22:19.599
Read between the lines.

00:22:20.162 --> 00:22:20.900
Pick up on what's not being said.

00:22:21.319 --> 00:22:21.914
These are skills you develop

00:22:22.099 --> 00:22:22.393
over time.

00:22:22.721 --> 00:22:23.220
Did you know

00:22:23.220 --> 00:22:23.531
that listening

00:22:25.523 --> 00:22:26.214
is actually a skill?

00:22:26.925 --> 00:22:27.394
Did you know that?

00:22:28.420 --> 00:22:28.633
Okay.

00:22:29.660 --> 00:22:30.630
So why don't we use it?

00:22:32.781 --> 00:22:33.529
Why are there people...

00:22:34.500 --> 00:22:35.680
I'll give you,

00:22:35.961 --> 00:22:36.898
I think I have some stats,

00:22:37.019 --> 00:22:37.213
I hope.

00:22:39.027 --> 00:22:39.599
I talked about it with the others.

00:22:40.662 --> 00:22:41.660
Listening is different from hearing.

00:22:42.944 --> 00:22:43.838
We get interrupted

00:22:44.242 --> 00:22:46.240
every 17 seconds.

00:22:48.145 --> 00:22:48.680
So that's why

00:22:48.680 --> 00:22:49.116
I'm using a timer.

00:22:50.487 --> 00:22:51.019
I'm starting the timer

00:22:52.104 --> 00:22:53.160
so you have one minute

00:22:53.808 --> 00:22:54.519
to introduce yourself

00:22:55.208 --> 00:22:55.720
and then,

00:22:56.203 --> 00:22:57.078
the other person introduces themselves

00:22:57.509 --> 00:22:57.940
and then,

00:22:58.119 --> 00:22:58.720
the other person introduces themselves.

00:22:58.820 --> 00:22:59.358
And in five minutes,

00:23:00.025 --> 00:23:00.638
who used the timer

00:23:00.700 --> 00:23:01.147
during the lunch break?

00:23:01.859 --> 00:23:02.477
Not yet.

00:23:02.740 --> 00:23:02.811
Okay.

00:23:03.263 --> 00:23:03.900
No one's taking action

00:23:03.900 --> 00:23:04.579
in this community.

00:23:05.684 --> 00:23:06.660
or maybe they're all downstairs,

00:23:06.660 --> 00:23:07.027
the advanced ones.

00:23:08.625 --> 00:23:09.259
I asked the question,

00:23:09.380 --> 00:23:09.834
there were a few more

00:23:10.039 --> 00:23:10.454
hands raised,

00:23:10.680 --> 00:23:11.460
but it still wasn't

00:23:11.460 --> 00:23:11.648
crazy.

00:23:13.046 --> 00:23:13.559
Why am I bothering you

00:23:13.559 --> 00:23:13.865
with the timer?

00:23:14.865 --> 00:23:15.559
Because I want to give you

00:23:15.807 --> 00:23:16.238
the opportunity

00:23:16.750 --> 00:23:17.179
to meet

00:23:17.220 --> 00:23:17.423
the partner,

00:23:19.204 --> 00:23:19.698
the investor,

00:23:20.506 --> 00:23:21.319
the project leader

00:23:21.768 --> 00:23:22.460
who's hiding out in this room.

00:23:24.144 --> 00:23:24.859
But if today,

00:23:24.940 --> 00:23:25.195
you're here

00:23:25.279 --> 00:23:26.079
and you start talking,

00:23:26.482 --> 00:23:27.019
you're in a group

00:23:27.019 --> 00:23:27.434
of three or four,

00:23:28.366 --> 00:23:28.779
and you start

00:23:28.925 --> 00:23:29.299
introducing yourself,

00:23:29.400 --> 00:23:29.599
there's always one guy,

00:23:29.599 --> 00:23:30.074
he cuts you off

00:23:30.319 --> 00:23:30.790
after 17 seconds.

00:23:31.339 --> 00:23:32.058
Has that never happened to you?

00:23:32.099 --> 00:23:32.395
There's a guy,

00:23:32.539 --> 00:23:32.740
he shows up,

00:23:32.819 --> 00:23:33.436
just barges in like that,

00:23:33.660 --> 00:23:33.873
he's there,

00:23:34.259 --> 00:23:34.348
bam,

00:23:34.845 --> 00:23:35.299
he grabs the spotlight,

00:23:35.420 --> 00:23:35.579
the other guy,

00:23:35.640 --> 00:23:36.053
starts talking

00:23:36.300 --> 00:23:36.758
with him and everything,

00:23:37.022 --> 00:23:37.740
You missed your chance.

00:23:37.759 --> 00:23:38.654
So, where do we go from here?

00:23:39.142 --> 00:23:40.599
You lost the opportunity.

00:23:41.741 --> 00:23:42.720
Who's ever found themselves

00:23:42.740 --> 00:23:43.338
in a situation like that,

00:23:43.420 --> 00:23:43.711
super frustrated

00:23:43.920 --> 00:23:44.392
because you couldn't finish

00:23:44.700 --> 00:23:45.258
what you wanted to say,

00:23:45.319 --> 00:23:45.759
because there are people

00:23:45.759 --> 00:23:46.039
who are there,

00:23:46.039 --> 00:23:46.526
just talking about their lives.

00:23:51.230 --> 00:23:51.380
Same thing,

00:23:51.400 --> 00:23:51.751
for you shy people.

00:23:54.112 --> 00:23:54.240
Me,

00:23:54.339 --> 00:23:54.713
speaking for a minute,

00:23:55.587 --> 00:23:55.940
right away,

00:23:56.140 --> 00:23:56.518
no way.

00:23:57.488 --> 00:23:57.818
Shy folks,

00:23:58.085 --> 00:23:58.539
you also need

00:23:58.539 --> 00:23:58.832
to speak up.

00:23:59.686 --> 00:23:59.819
So,

00:24:00.125 --> 00:24:00.499
it's important.

00:24:00.900 --> 00:24:01.039
So,

00:24:01.163 --> 00:24:01.440
listening,

00:24:01.539 --> 00:24:01.880
that's important too,

00:24:01.980 --> 00:24:02.680
It's a skill.

00:24:03.025 --> 00:24:03.279
Listening,

00:24:03.400 --> 00:24:03.759
it's the words,

00:24:03.839 --> 00:24:04.096
the looks,

00:24:04.240 --> 00:24:04.557
the intentions,

00:24:04.740 --> 00:24:05.200
the real reasons.

00:24:05.319 --> 00:24:05.756
Information,

00:24:06.284 --> 00:24:07.259
is the most important asset

00:24:07.987 --> 00:24:08.599
when you're negotiating.

00:24:09.511 --> 00:24:09.619
So,

00:24:10.266 --> 00:24:10.919
if you're talking,

00:24:11.683 --> 00:24:12.400
you've already lost, in my book.

00:24:14.223 --> 00:24:15.180
When you start negotiating,

00:24:15.279 --> 00:24:15.734
the very first thing

00:24:15.900 --> 00:24:16.073
to do,

00:24:16.279 --> 00:24:16.916
is ask questions

00:24:17.039 --> 00:24:17.400
so that people

00:24:17.400 --> 00:24:17.714
answer you.

00:24:18.799 --> 00:24:19.579
Because that's the only way

00:24:19.579 --> 00:24:19.891
you'll find out

00:24:20.467 --> 00:24:21.119
what makes them tick,

00:24:21.480 --> 00:24:22.237
what they really want to do.

00:24:23.267 --> 00:24:23.759
But you have to do it.

00:24:24.488 --> 00:24:24.819
You'll see,

00:24:24.980 --> 00:24:25.298
it's going to be tough

00:24:25.339 --> 00:24:25.917
for some of you.

00:24:26.180 --> 00:24:26.440
Honestly,

00:24:26.519 --> 00:24:27.179
I'm challenging you right now

00:24:27.665 --> 00:24:28.596
during the networking breaks,

00:24:28.980 --> 00:24:29.519
you'll see.

00:24:30.826 --> 00:24:31.200
Around you,

00:24:31.279 --> 00:24:32.217
the people who never stop

00:24:32.400 --> 00:24:32.653
talking,

00:24:32.980 --> 00:24:33.297
blah blah and all that,

00:24:33.460 --> 00:24:33.920
it's not necessarily...

00:24:33.920 --> 00:24:34.140
You see,

00:24:35.486 --> 00:24:36.378
you really need to master this.

00:24:37.460 --> 00:24:37.696
So,

00:24:37.962 --> 00:24:38.500
let me give you an example.

00:24:38.923 --> 00:24:39.339
Listening,

00:24:39.880 --> 00:24:40.160
a skill,

00:24:40.339 --> 00:24:40.779
let me give you an example.

00:24:40.920 --> 00:24:41.059
So this,

00:24:41.059 --> 00:24:41.266
is Erin

00:24:42.126 --> 00:24:42.799
sending me a message,

00:24:42.960 --> 00:24:43.631
who's one of our agents

00:24:44.140 --> 00:24:44.608
at Bonaparte in Dubai.

00:24:45.900 --> 00:24:46.276
So here,

00:24:46.440 --> 00:24:46.579
she says to me

00:24:46.579 --> 00:24:47.134
"Hi Jean-Guillaume,

00:24:47.440 --> 00:24:48.059
It's Erin from Bonaparte,

00:24:48.099 --> 00:24:48.515
I've got an investor

00:24:48.640 --> 00:24:49.092
who's looking to invest

00:24:49.400 --> 00:24:50.294
between 25 and 50 million dirhams,

00:24:50.740 --> 00:24:51.717
so that's between 6 and 15 million dollars,

00:24:53.347 --> 00:24:53.798
for a project

00:24:54.085 --> 00:24:54.960
redevelopment deal.

00:24:55.462 --> 00:24:56.558
I'm going to show him the tours,

00:24:56.759 --> 00:24:56.946
Albarari,

00:24:58.131 --> 00:24:58.460
the quality,

00:24:58.579 --> 00:24:58.953
the finishes.

00:24:59.339 --> 00:24:59.738
I'd like to set up

00:25:00.949 --> 00:25:01.559
a call with you

00:25:02.285 --> 00:25:02.798
to talk about

00:25:02.819 --> 00:25:04.079
strategy options.

00:25:04.669 --> 00:25:05.099
I know

00:25:05.201 --> 00:25:06.159
you're out of the country,

00:25:06.440 --> 00:25:07.019
but we can still

00:25:07.019 --> 00:25:07.332
set up a call,

00:25:07.642 --> 00:25:07.730
etc.

00:25:08.579 --> 00:25:08.680
That's it.

00:25:09.380 --> 00:25:09.539
Alright.

00:25:11.145 --> 00:25:11.640
She just got here.

00:25:13.025 --> 00:25:13.819
She's doing her job well

00:25:13.839 --> 00:25:14.316
because it's a guy

00:25:14.705 --> 00:25:15.259
super qualified.

00:25:15.945 --> 00:25:16.519
But right now I don't have enough

00:25:16.765 --> 00:25:17.460
information today

00:25:17.460 --> 00:25:18.116
to know if I'm the one

00:25:18.240 --> 00:25:18.859
who should talk to him, etc.

00:25:19.059 --> 00:25:19.534
So my question is,

00:25:19.880 --> 00:25:20.833
what's his profile?

00:25:21.544 --> 00:25:22.256
What's his timeline?

00:25:22.704 --> 00:25:23.380
When does he want his return

00:25:23.585 --> 00:25:24.115
on investment?

00:25:24.525 --> 00:25:25.240
How much of a return

00:25:25.259 --> 00:25:25.654
on investment

00:25:25.799 --> 00:25:26.209
is he expecting?

00:25:26.945 --> 00:25:27.519
Is the money,

00:25:27.682 --> 00:25:28.479
already available

